    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 27, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. For Finley.<note n="5" xml:id="d261fn5">Harold D. Finley, Assistant Chief of
                        the Division of the American Republics.</note> My letter January 24
                    regarding reduction in interest rate.<note n="6" xml:id="d261fn6">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Dana Munro<note n="7" xml:id="d261fn7">Vice president of the Foreign Bondholders
                        Protective Council.</note> expressed to me yesterday the opinion that the
                    fiscal agent would be obliged to pay interest up to 6% on the April 1 coupon if
                    he has sufficient funds for that purpose. In these circumstances and since funds
                    have already been remitted for the payment of 4% interest on the April 1 coupon
                    the conclusion of an accord prior to February 1 would appear to be urgent so
                    that the fiscal representative may legally withhold further remittances to the
                    fiscal agent on account of the April 1 coupon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
